parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward
the speedometer reading goes from 60 to 0
the overdrive light flashes on and off
the check engine light is on
the transmission makes a loud noise or clunking sound
the vehicle feels like it's in neutral
the transmission fails to shift properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power control module can cause the engine to take a long time to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The engine takes a long time to start
the power control module is defective.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle bucks or jerks while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes make unusual noises
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the brakes are spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignoring the check engine light can lead to further engine damage, causing the vehicle to break down or fail, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle's performance is affected
the vehicle's fuel efficiency is decreased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seat belt failure can cause the vehicle's occupants to be unrestrained in the event of a crash, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt light comes on
the seat belt is stuck or jammed
the seat belt does not restrain the occupant properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of brake pressure, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake fluid leakage
soft or spongy brake pedal

vehicle takes longer to stop
whistling noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop or fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle takes longer to stop
brakes are not tight enough
ABS light stays on
intermittent brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or shift gears unexpectedly, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Transmission jerks or shifts gears unexpectedly
check engine light appears on the dashboard
vehicle hesitates or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealership to honor the manufacturer's recall can lead to unresolved safety issues, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Difficulty in getting the dealership to honor the recall
unavailability of parts
inability to provide a proper appointment.
